AB  - This study examines the relationship between Indian academic librarians' attitude towards generative artificial intelligence (AI) and their intentions to adopt it in professional practice. This mixed-methods research gathered data from 497 academic librarians across Indian institutions through an online survey, which was analyzed through the lens of the Unified Theory of Acceptance and Use of Technology (UTAUT). The causal relationship between UTAUT factors, attitude and behavioural intentions was tested through Partial Least Squares Structural Equation Modelling (PLS-SEM). Social Influence emerged as the strongest predicting UTAUT factor, with perceived usage effort of generative AI, perceived usefulness of AI and facilitating conditions also contributing towards attitude formation, which in turn influences behavioural intentions to adopt generative AI. This research establishes attitude as a mediator between UTAUT factors and behavioural intentions for AI adoption in Indian academic libraries. Factors like limited budgets and lack of managerial support present challenges for adoption of AI despite positive attitudes, indicating a need for greater involvement from senior management for adoption of innovations like generative AI. © 2026
